  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The deposit contract needs to actually verify that the deposit data is **exactly** 192 bytes long (that's `len(ssz_serialize(deposit_data))`), 192 = 8 (amount) + 8 (timestamp) + 48 (pubkey) + 32 (withdrawal credentials) + 96 (proof of possession).\r\n\r\nThe reason is that if a deposit data is submitted that is NOT 192 bytes, it is impossible to create a DepositData that serializes to the hash put into the Merkle branch, which could be used to prevent progress of deposit processing.",
