    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Note that `ssz_serialize(deposit_data)` currently includes a 4-byte length prefix.\r\n\r\n@protolambda notes that any composite object (container, list, tuple) can contain a variable-length sub-object by embedding a list. We can't really put length prefixes everywhere because serialising something as trivial as a chunk list `byte[32][]` would have an overhead of 4 bytes per chunk.\r\n\r\nTo solve the `ssz_serialize(deposit_data)` length prefix issue, and the overhead issue from superfluous length prefixes, my suggestion is to only add a length prefix for variable-size containers/lists/tuples, i.e. containers/lists/tuples that embed a list. Thoughts?",
